00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:50,190
他们对你好吗
You've been treated well?

182
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,320
很好  如您所见
Very well, as you can see.

183
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,050
谢谢  利特斯基先生
Thank you, Mr. Litsky,

184
00:10:54,050 --> 00:10:56,150
但我想听科里根先生自己说
but I'd like to hear it from Mr. Corrigan.

185
00:10:56,630 --> 00:10:58,610
是的  他们对我很好
Yes, they've treated me well.

186
00:10:59,370 --> 00:11:02,310
-你看过医生吗  -昨天看过
- You've seen a doctor? - I have. Yesterday.

187
00:11:03,420 --> 00:11:06,320
-你看起来很瘦  -我一直很瘦
- You look thin. - I've always been thin.

188
00:11:08,210 --> 00:11:10,200
总统让我亲自过来
The president asked me to see you in person

189
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,630
告诉你这个好消息
to share the good news.

190
00:11:12,140 --> 00:11:14,220
你的释放条款已经敲定了
The terms of your release have been finalized.

191
00:11:14,220 --> 00:11:16,700
我们明天就带你回家
We'll be bringing you home with us tomorrow.

192
00:11:18,710 --> 00:11:20,160
我以为你会高兴
I thought you'd be pleased.

193
00:11:20,170 --> 00:11:21,830
条款是什么
What are the terms?

194
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:24,830
我们会举行联合新闻发布会
There will be a joint press conference.

195
00:11:25,210 --> 00:11:28,390
-跟佩特罗夫吗  -是的  两位总统一起
- With Petrov? - Yes, both presidents.

196
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:33,290
协议要求你做一个简短声明
The agreement asks that you make a brief statement.

197
00:11:35,690 --> 00:11:39,230
抱歉  字太小  我也没戴眼镜
I'm sorry, um, the type is too small and I don't have glasses.

198
00:11:39,230 --> 00:11:41,920
-我们为科里根先生提供了眼镜  -是的
- We offered glasses to Mr. Corrigan-- - They did.

199
00:11:42,430 --> 00:11:44,300
我的在被拘捕时弄坏了
Mine broke during the arrest.

200
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:46,560
其他犯人没有眼镜
The other inmates don't get glasses.

201
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:48,580
我不想受特殊待遇
I didn't want special treatment.

202
00:11:48,590 --> 00:11:52,070
我们为所有需要的人提供眼镜  不论国际
We provide glasses to anyone who needs them, Russian or American.

203
00:11:52,070 --> 00:11:53,630
这是个谎言
That is a lie.

204
00:11:54,420 --> 00:11:55,460
我读给你听
I will read it.

205
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,630
上面写着  "我  迈克尔·科里根
It says, "I, Michael Corrigan,

206
00:11:58,630 --> 00:12:01,410
就违反俄罗斯联邦法律
apologize to the citizens of the Russian Federation

207
00:12:01,410 --> 00:12:02,950
向俄国公民道歉
for breaking your laws.

208
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:05,530
我不该向未成年人
I regret my part in exposing minors

209
00:12:05,530 --> 00:12:07,820
宣扬非传统性取向
to nontraditional sexual attitudes.

210
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:10,240
我很感谢佩特罗夫总统
I am grateful to President Petrov

211
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:12,850
宽容地释放了我
for the clemency my release demonstrates,

212
00:12:13,830 --> 00:12:16,840
并允许我回到美国"
and for allowing me to return to the United States."

213
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:19,230
谁写的
Who wrote it?

214
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:21,120
这是国务院
It's the result of extended negotiations

215
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:22,970
与俄罗斯外交部之间
between representatives of the State Department

216
00:12:22,970 --> 00:12:25,370
深入谈判后的结果
and the Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs.

217
00:12:26,230 --> 00:12:27,770
抱歉  我不能做这个声明
I'm sorry, I can't say it.

218
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:30,730
我知道情况很不理想  迈克尔
I know it's far from ideal, Michael.

219
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:34,820
除非废除法律  不然不可能理想
There is no ideal. Other than repealing the law.

220
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:39,980
能让我们单独待会儿吗
May we have a moment?

221
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:44,630
佩特罗夫总统让我陪着您
President Petrov asked me to remain with you.

222
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,730
我请你让我们单独待一会儿
And I'm asking you to give us a moment.

223
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:57,850
利特斯基先生  这间牢房被监听了吧
Mr. Litsky? I'm assuming this cell is bugged?

224
00:12:58,770 --> 00:13:01,260
我对这里并不了解
I know nothing about the facilities.

225
00:13:01,260 --> 00:13:04,080
-在哪里  -安德伍德夫人
- Where is it? - Mrs. Underwood.

226
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:07,930
科里根先生和我要想真正地单独谈话
If Mr. Corrigan and I are to speak privately,

227
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:11,050
我需要保证对话的私密性
I would like to be assured that it is truly private.

228
00:13:11,050 --> 00:13:12,450
告诉我监听设备在哪里
Show me where the bug is.

229
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,560
进来
Подойти.

230
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:22,660
安德伍德夫人要求拆掉监听器
Госпожа Андервуд просила убрать микрофон.

231
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:25,060
如果可以的话  这就拆
Прямо сейчас, если можно.

232
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:34,750
谢谢
Thank you.

233
00:13:46,590 --> 00:13:48,840
他们不可能废除法律
They're not going to repeal the law.

234
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:52,120
你必须发表声明才能被释放
The statement is a prerequisite for your release.

235
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:54,420
没有商量的余地了  迈克尔
There are no negotiations here, Michael.

236
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:56,110
谈判已经结束了
That part already happened.

237
00:13:56,110 --> 00:13:57,760
其他27个人呢
What about the 27 others?

238
00:13:58,050 --> 00:13:59,340
他们不是美国人
They're not American.

239
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,040
如果不释放他们  我也不该被释放
Well, if they're not gonna be released, neither should I.

240
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:04,060
对于他们我们无能为力
There's nothing we can do for them.

241
00:14:05,210 --> 00:14:09,580
你是第一夫人  还是美国驻联合国大使
You're the First Lady, and the ambassador to the United Nations.

242
00:14:09,580 --> 00:14:11,350
你却告诉我你无能为力
And you're telling me there's nothing you can do?

243
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:12,990
我不相信
I refuse to believe that.

244
00:14:12,990 --> 00:14:16,200
迈克尔  争取到你的释放就已经很艰难了
Michael, it was hard enough to negotiate just for your release.

245
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,410
恐怕你得把我拖出去了
You'll have to drag me out of here

246
00:14:17,410 --> 00:14:19,050
因为我不会做那个声明
because I'm not giving that statement.

247
00:14:19,050 --> 00:14:20,220
这只是几句话
It's just words.

248
00:14:21,020 --> 00:14:24,390
等一回到美国本土  你就可以否认这些话
Words you can disown the moment you're back on US soil.

249
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,230
佩特罗夫的反同法
Petrov's gay propaganda law?

250
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,280
那也只是言语
That's just words, too.

251
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:32,780
指挥与控制权的轮换
So, command and control rotation.

252
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:34,500
第一年之后每半年一次
Semi-annually, after the first year.

253
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:36,290
我们希望能立即轮换
We pushed for immediate rotation,

254
00:14:36,290 --> 00:14:38,430
-可是以色列人...  -当然
- but the Israelis have-- - No, of course.

255
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:40,020
我们需要赢得他们的信任
We need to earn their trust.

256
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:42,320
但是  做出任何重大决定之前
But we would never make any major decisions

257
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:44,290
我们都会先跟你的上将商量
without consulting your generals first.

258
00:14:44,290 --> 00:14:47,390
只要能保证透明性  保持沟通就好
As long as there is transparency and communication.

259
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:49,470
这正是整个项目的关键
Well, that's the key to this entire enterprise.

260
00:14:50,410 --> 00:14:53,340
只要平安度过第一年
Then after the first year is fine and, uh...

261
00:14:53,490 --> 00:14:55,930
驻军数量也合适
troop numbers look agreeable,

262
00:14:56,350 --> 00:14:59,700
你能保证派来这个数目吗
are you sure you can procure this many on your end?

263
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:01,840
是的  我不需要通过国会
Yes. I don't need Congress for that.

264
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:04,000
的确  但资金怎么解决
No, but the funding.

265
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,500
与其他派驻一样从国防预算里拨
It comes out of the DOD budget like any regular deployment.

266
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:10,350
至于你方军队的基础设施建设和后勤
Now, infrastructure and logistical supplies for your troops,

267
00:15:10,350 --> 00:15:13,670
这份支出可以算作辅助设施
well, we can add that expense as ancillary support.

268
00:15:14,470 --> 00:15:15,570
我们能出点
We can pitch in.

269
00:15:15,570 --> 00:15:18,500
不管你们能拿出多少我们当然都欢迎
Well, whatever you could spare would certainly be welcome.

270
00:15:19,090 --> 00:15:22,550
不过还有一件我们都在考虑的事
But... that brings us to the elephant in the room.

271
00:15:22,550 --> 00:15:23,850
导弹防御
Missile defense.

272
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:27,190
我能接受波兰那边的部分削减
Now, I can accept a partial scale-back in Poland.

273
00:15:27,190 --> 00:15:29,620
这可以不公开
And it doesn't have to be... announced.

274
00:15:29,620 --> 00:15:32,790
可我们得考虑捷克方面
But we need to consider the Czech Republic.

275
00:15:32,980 --> 00:15:34,250
说说你的顾虑
Tell me your concerns.

276
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:38,460
我说了不要打断我们
Я просил нас не беспокоить.

277
00:16:00,690 --> 00:16:02,820
你夫人很重视隐私啊
Your wife values privacy.

278
00:16:03,450 --> 00:16:04,390
你说什么
Excuse me?

279
00:16:06,060 --> 00:16:08,760
我们正谈导弹防御呢
We were talking missile defense.

280
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,390
怎么提起克莱尔了
Why did you bring up Claire?

281
00:16:10,390 --> 00:16:15,010
她正与科里根密谈  没什么大不了的
She's... talking privately to Corrigan. It's no matter.

282
00:16:15,790 --> 00:16:17,200
出什么问题了吗
Is there something wrong?

283
00:16:17,610 --> 00:16:18,680
希望没有
I hope not.

284
00:16:20,370 --> 00:16:23,050
回到导弹防御上来吧
Now, missile defense.

285
00:16:23,860 --> 00:16:27,150
就是一份说给俄国媒体听的声明而已
A statement for the Russian media. That's all it is.

286
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:28,420
我问你
Let me ask you something.

287
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:32,660
你要是我的话  会读这份声明吗
Would you read that statement if you were me?

288
00:16:32,660 --> 00:16:34,040
是的  我会读的
Yes, I would.

289
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:38,290
你会感谢一个说你对孩子有威胁的人
You'd thank a man who says you're dangerous to children?

290
00:16:39,110 --> 00:16:42,480
不必出自真心  只需说出来
You don't have to mean it. You just have to say it.

291
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:52,120
我绝食抗议了六天
I went on a hunger strike for six days.

292
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:54,700
然后我停了下来
Then I stopped.

293
00:16:56,010 --> 00:16:59,150
饥饿使我难以坚持
Too hungry. I couldn't go on.

294
00:16:59,990 --> 00:17:03,840
跟我一起被捕的  有个叫塞尔盖的
One of the others that, uh, I was arrested with, Sergei,

295
00:17:04,330 --> 00:17:06,570
他坚持了28天
hung in there for 28 days.

296
00:17:08,650 --> 00:17:10,770
他们决定强迫他进食
They decided to force-feed him,

297
00:17:10,770 --> 00:17:13,620
并终于同意他母亲看望他
and they finally agreed to let his mother visit.

298
00:17:13,910 --> 00:17:16,800
可这都太晚了
Turns out it was too late, on both counts.

299
00:17:17,490 --> 00:17:19,800
关于我的新闻铺天盖地
Lots of news stories about me.

300
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,500
却没有关于塞尔盖的
None about Sergei.

301
00:17:22,610 --> 00:17:26,080
一个人就这么悄无声息地死了
A man dies and it's like nothing happened.

302
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:28,080
就因为他是俄国人
Because he's Russian.

303
00:17:30,010 --> 00:17:32,830
我不能抛弃其他被捕的人
I can't abandon the others in here.

304
00:17:33,590 --> 00:17:36,630
还有外面成千上万
Or the millions of people out there

305
00:17:36,630 --> 00:17:40,250
被人说他们生来就有问题的人
who are told the way they are born is wrong.

306
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:42,850
但回家后你可以讲出塞尔盖的故事
But back home, you can share Sergei's story.

307
00:17:42,850 --> 00:17:44,990
这对他或其他人无济于事
That doesn't do anything for him or the others.

308
00:17:58,370 --> 00:18:00,300
如果有必要  我们会把你拖出去
We will drag you out if necessary.

309
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:02,110
在这事上你无力反抗
You don't have any power over that.

310
00:18:02,110 --> 00:18:04,040
但是  我可以自主的
But the one thing I do have power over

311
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:05,920
是不发表这份声明
is not making that statement.

312
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:06,720
好吧
Okay.

313
00:18:09,220 --> 00:18:12,640
那如果我让他们修改
What if I can get them to change the line

314
00:18:12,980 --> 00:18:15,030
关于非传统性取向这句呢
about nontraditional sexual attitudes?

315
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:16,200
这才是最困扰你的部分  对吧
That's what bothers you most, right?

316
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:18,720
这不是文字游戏  要么做到底  要么不做
You can't parse this. It's all or nothing.

317
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,410
政治不是这么搞的
That's not how politics works.

318
00:18:20,410 --> 00:18:22,430
但革命都是这样的
But it's how revolution works!

319
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:27,330
进展怎么样了
How are things going?

320
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:31,190
我能跟你说句话吗
May I speak with you for a moment?

321
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:40,160
如果达不成一致  那就算了  就这样
Что если не будет согласования. То и будет и пусть. Все.

322
00:18:52,020 --> 00:18:54,970
-你有什么目的  -你指什么
- What are you up to? - What do you mean?

323
00:18:54,970 --> 00:18:55,780
科里根
Corrigan.

324
00:18:58,040 --> 00:18:58,880
告诉我发生什么了
Tell me what's wrong.

325
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:01,220
你就希望他拒绝  从而使我难堪
You wanted him to refuse. To embarrass me.

326
00:19:01,220 --> 00:19:02,860
你夫人叫他拒绝发表声明
Your wife told him not to make the statement.

327
00:19:02,860 --> 00:19:04,110
简直荒唐
That is ludicrous.

328
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:06,500
你是带着虚情假意而来
You came here with false intentions.

329
00:19:06,500 --> 00:19:09,160
不  维克多  我们都料到他会很顽固
No. Viktor, we knew that he might be stubborn.

330
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:11,470
但此人毕竟信念坚定
But this is a man with strong beliefs.

331
00:19:17,350 --> 00:19:19,180
这份声明对我意义重大
This statement is important to me.

332
00:19:19,180 --> 00:19:21,940
克莱尔肯定正努力说服他发表声明
Well, if anything, Claire is trying to convince him to make it.

333
00:19:21,940 --> 00:19:25,180
那为什么她要求把监听设备拿走
Then why did she ask for the surveillance audio to be removed?

334
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:27,380
我不知道
I don't know.

335
00:19:27,780 --> 00:19:29,670
或许是想让他放松
Perhaps so he wouldn't feel on the spot.

336
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:32,480
但是  不用担心这些
But, look, I wouldn't worry about this just yet.

337
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,220
克莱尔很有说服力
Claire is very persuasive.

338
00:19:34,220 --> 00:19:36,050
我把话说明白
Let me be very clear.

339
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:39,000
他不发表声明  任何协议都免谈
If there is no statement, there is no deal on any front.

340
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,040
我们的协议  关于他的协议都取消
Not between us. Not for him.

341
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:43,440
他会接受审判  被定罪  被判决
He gets tried, convicted, sentenced.

342
00:19:46,010 --> 00:19:50,430
我已经让利特斯基先生通知他们了
Now, I asked Mr. Litsky to inform them both.

343
00:19:50,810 --> 00:19:53,080
我对我妻子信心十足
I have complete confidence in my wife.

344
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:56,860
维克多  你要清楚  这不是什么计划的一部分
And Viktor, you must know, this isn't part of any plan.

345
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,230
就这样
That's it.

346
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:15,190
这份声明没有讨价还价的余地
There's no flexibility with regard to the statement.

347
00:20:15,190 --> 00:20:17,130
你不配合就得接受审判
You don't cooperate, you go to trial.

348
00:20:17,590 --> 00:20:20,290
正好  他们不能阻止我在法庭上发声
Good. They can't keep me from speaking in court.

349
00:20:21,870 --> 00:20:23,330
那你丈夫怎么办
What about your husband?

350
00:20:25,210 --> 00:20:26,630
你和约翰谈过了
You've spoken to John?

351
00:20:27,460 --> 00:20:29,110
我跟他说我们抱很大希望
I let him know we were hopeful.

352
00:20:32,030 --> 00:20:32,820
他怎么样了
How is he?

353
00:20:34,120 --> 00:20:35,310
他很担心你
He's worried about you.

354
00:20:39,660 --> 00:20:40,840
他本想跟我们一起来
He wanted to come with us,

355
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:43,270
但这明显不可能
but that wasn't possible, for obvious reasons.

356
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:46,090
我保证见过你就给他打电话
I promised to call after I saw you.

357
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:55,390
我其实想让你在空军一号上亲自给他打电话
