And the guy is putting all 12 of us to sleep.

534
00:30:00,270 --> 00:30:04,600
他说的话确实有道理  但毫无号召力
What he was saying made sense, but... zero charisma.

535
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:06,860
甚至可以说是排斥力
It was worse: anti-charisma.

536
00:30:08,020 --> 00:30:10,380
但我注意到他有一个习惯
But I noticed he had this habit of, uh...

537
00:30:11,180 --> 00:30:14,110
当他说到重点时会歪头
tilting his head when he was making an important point.

538
00:30:14,110 --> 00:30:17,620
真的很惹人爱
It was... it was so endearing.

539
00:30:18,930 --> 00:30:19,930
就像这样
It was like this.

540
00:30:21,510 --> 00:30:22,470
像这样
Like...

541
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:26,260
我无法控制自己  当场就爱上了他
I couldn't help it. I fell in love with him right then and there.

542
00:30:26,260 --> 00:30:27,350
演讲人是约翰
This was John?

543
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:32,470
真是恍如隔世
A long time ago, in a galaxy far, far away.

544
00:30:33,410 --> 00:30:35,690
电视上的他挺有号召力的
Well, he's pretty charismatic on TV.

545
00:30:35,690 --> 00:30:38,620
他学会了如何号召别人  我学会了如何思考
He learned charisma. I learned how to think.

546
00:30:39,370 --> 00:30:41,200
我们互相磨合得不错
We rubbed off on each other well.

547
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,960
我不知道你们在一起这么久了
I didn't know you'd been together so long.

548
00:30:43,430 --> 00:30:44,610
21年
Twenty-one years.

549
00:30:44,610 --> 00:30:48,580
只结婚了五年  因为之前我们没法结
Only been married for five because, well, we couldn't earlier.

550
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:52,270
弗兰西斯和我刚庆祝完28周年结婚纪念日
Francis and I just celebrated 28.

551
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:54,300
超过你半辈子了
Over half your life.

552
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:58,490
没错  我还从未这么想过
That's true. I haven't even thought about that.

553
00:30:58,810 --> 00:30:59,730
你结婚时还很年轻
You were young.

554
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:02,370
22岁
Twenty-two.

555
00:31:04,300 --> 00:31:05,830
你后悔过吗
You ever regret it?

556
00:31:07,080 --> 00:31:09,740
不  不后悔  我爱弗兰西斯
No. No. I love Francis.

557
00:31:10,460 --> 00:31:11,720
如今更甚以往
Now more than ever.

558
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:13,260
我后悔了
I regret it.

559
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:17,590
在还未完全了解自己之前就与人定下终身
Committing to someone before I even knew who I was.

560
00:31:17,930 --> 00:31:18,970
我们并未进行合法宣誓
We didn't take legal vows,

561
00:31:18,970 --> 00:31:21,170
但我们有自己的方式
but we had our own version.

562
00:31:22,130 --> 00:31:24,470
-真的很傻  -为什么
- Stupid. - Why?

563
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:28,500
因为我给他的就只有伤害
Because all I've ever done is hurt him.

564
00:31:29,660 --> 00:31:32,990
让他待在我背后  劈腿  各种各样
Um, kept him in my shadow, cheated on him, you name it.

565
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:35,620
两人相濡以沫的岁月最重要
Well, it's the history that counts,

566
00:31:35,620 --> 00:31:37,280
而非其他事情  对吧
not the other things, right?

567
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:39,840
没错  过去无可替代
That's true. No substitute for history.

568
00:31:41,040 --> 00:31:43,490
但对他不公平
But it's unfair to him.

569
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:46,980
我不相信公平
I don't believe in fairness.

570
00:31:47,730 --> 00:31:50,910
我认为你也不相信  即便你在为之奋斗
I don't think you do either, even though you fight for it.

571
00:31:50,920 --> 00:31:53,540
我不相信你对你丈夫的爱更甚以往
And I don't believe you love your husband more than ever.

572
00:31:53,540 --> 00:31:55,280
你怎么知道
How could you possibly know?

573
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:56,570
将心比心
Takes one to know one.

574
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:02,870
约翰和我已经两年没上过床了
John and I haven't slept with each other in almost two years.

575
00:32:02,870 --> 00:32:04,690
我们甚至都分房睡了
We don't even sleep in the same bedroom.

576
00:32:05,060 --> 00:32:07,780
我们谈过分居的事  但终究没那么做
We've talked about separating, but we never follow through.

577
00:32:08,790 --> 00:32:11,490
为了婚姻平等努力至今  我们自己却离婚了
It seems wrong to fight this hard for marriage equality

578
00:32:11,490 --> 00:32:13,100
感觉不太好
and then get divorced.

579
00:32:13,620 --> 00:32:14,780
于事业无益
Bad for business.

580
00:32:16,360 --> 00:32:18,600
说实话  我认为这违背人性
Honestly, I don't think it's how humans are built.

581
00:32:19,350 --> 00:32:22,020
在一起五十年  白头偕老
To be with each other for 50 years.

582
00:32:23,530 --> 00:32:25,900
你也没得选  对吧
You don't have that option either, do you?

583
00:32:25,900 --> 00:32:26,700
什么意思
How do you mean?

584
00:32:26,890 --> 00:32:28,500
如果你不想继续下去
Well, if you wanted something else,

585
00:32:28,500 --> 00:32:30,880
对你们的事业会是致命打击
that would be really bad for business.

586
00:32:33,630 --> 00:32:34,660
你得吃点东西
You should eat.

587
00:32:35,100 --> 00:32:36,820
蛇对夏娃也这么说
Said the snake to Eve.

588
00:32:36,830 --> 00:32:39,720
吃你的苹果吧  世界不会就此终结
Eat your apple. The world won't end.

589
00:32:47,910 --> 00:32:50,100
你得给你夫人打电话让她离开
You need to get on the phone and tell her to leave.

590
00:32:50,100 --> 00:32:51,980
即便我打了她也不会听
She wouldn't listen to me even if I did.

591
00:32:51,980 --> 00:32:55,710
她现在一门心思要为你说服这家伙
She's dead set on convincing this guy for your benefit.

592
00:32:55,710 --> 00:32:58,470
必要的话  我会让保安护送她出来
I'll have the guards escort her out if necessary.

593
00:32:58,480 --> 00:33:01,400
他们休想动我夫人一根手指
They will not lay a finger on my wife.

594
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:04,920
你其实更希望如此吧
You'd actually prefer that, wouldn't you?

595
00:33:05,730 --> 00:33:06,770
这样你就能告诉全世界
So you could tell the world

596
00:33:06,770 --> 00:33:08,980
我们拉着第一夫人的头发  把她拽了出来
we dragged the First Lady out by her hair.

597
00:33:09,330 --> 00:33:12,650
我实在是越来越难以忍受你的多疑
I'm finding it more and more difficult to tolerate your paranoia.

598
00:33:12,650 --> 00:33:14,810
我对你的谎言也一样
I could say the same of your lies.

599
00:33:15,210 --> 00:33:17,640
我撒谎时  你绝不会发现
When I lie to you, you'll never know it,

600
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:19,510
而且肯定是有个好理由
and it will be for a good reason.

601
00:33:19,510 --> 00:33:22,030
科里根可不算
Corrigan doesn't fall into that category.

602
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:28,620
我就不该邀请你来访问
I should never have invited you here.

603
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:33,410
你我可以协作  今天下午就是证明
You and I can work together. This afternoon is proof.

604
00:33:33,410 --> 00:33:35,590
我就应该坚守我的立场
I would've been better off holding my ground.

605
00:33:35,590 --> 00:33:37,500
然后逼我们通过决议案吗
And forcing us to pass the resolution?

606
00:33:37,500 --> 00:33:40,050
联合国  我才不把他们放在心上
The United Nations? They mean nothing to me.

607
00:33:40,050 --> 00:33:43,190
如果真是这样  你就会坚守立场了
If they meant nothing to you, you would have held your ground.

608
00:33:43,190 --> 00:33:46,810
但你希望在国外和在国内一样受到尊敬
But you want to be respected abroad as much as you are at home.

609
00:33:46,810 --> 00:33:50,420
而我是怀着敬意而来  维克多
And I came here out of respect, Viktor.

610
00:33:50,670 --> 00:33:52,620
我对你的处境感同身受
And I sympathize with the situation you're in.

611
00:33:52,620 --> 00:33:53,700
我们都深陷其中
That we're both in.

612
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:56,690
不要让迈克尔·科里根
Let's not let Michael Corrigan

613
00:33:56,890 --> 00:34:00,160
决定国际形势的走向
dictate the course of nations.

614
00:34:04,210 --> 00:34:06,600
我们至少讨论下
Can we at least discuss

615
00:34:06,600 --> 00:34:09,770
如果由我发言应该怎么说
what a statement from me might look like?

616
00:34:13,100 --> 00:34:14,750
你看上去精疲力竭
You look exhausted.

617
00:34:16,130 --> 00:34:18,230
我在飞机上没怎么睡
I didn't sleep much on the plane, so...

618
00:34:18,870 --> 00:34:20,190
你回去吧
You should go back.

619
00:34:20,490 --> 00:34:22,630
你没必要跟我一起待在这里
There's no reason for you to be in here with me.

620
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:25,510
我不会走的
I'm not leaving.

621
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:28,800
你比我还固执呢
You're more stubborn than I am.

622
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:30,630
你为什么不让我帮你呢
Why won't you let me help you?

623
00:34:31,660 --> 00:34:33,460
我的要求很明确
I've made my demands clear.

624
00:34:36,510 --> 00:34:38,080
迈克尔  我告诉你如果你不肯
Michael, let me tell you what's going to happen

625
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:40,240
发表声明会发生什么吧
if you refuse to make this statement.

626
00:34:40,640 --> 00:34:41,920
你谁都帮不了
You'll help no one.

627
00:34:42,210 --> 00:34:43,810
事实上  其他那些跟你
In fact, life will get worse

628
00:34:43,810 --> 00:34:45,780
一起被捕的人会陷入更糟的境地
for the others you were arrested with.

629
00:34:46,130 --> 00:34:48,510
佩特罗夫会感到丢脸  会逮捕更多人
Petrov will feel embarrassed. He will arrest more people.

630
00:34:48,510 --> 00:34:50,330
会通过更可怕的法律
He will pass worse laws.

631
00:34:50,820 --> 00:34:54,670
他不会让一个美国的同性恋左右他的政策
He's not going to let some American homosexual dictate his policy.

632
00:34:55,450 --> 00:34:57,300
此人十分无情
This man is ruthless.

633
00:34:58,030 --> 00:35:00,150
你以为如果这事不成
You think he's gonna become reasonable suddenly

634
00:35:00,150 --> 00:35:01,330
他就会突然讲理了吗
when all of this falls apart?

635
00:35:01,330 --> 00:35:02,750
你太天真了
You're being naive!

636
00:35:03,170 --> 00:35:05,710
而且你还让别人为你的天真付出代价
And you're letting other people suffer because of it.

637
00:35:06,430 --> 00:35:10,190
别毁掉你一直以来的努力
Don't undo what you've fought so hard for.

638
00:35:10,190 --> 00:35:12,990
你以为你能激我同意吗  你做不到
You think you can shame me. But you can't.

639
00:35:12,990 --> 00:35:15,180
我是在告诉你实话
I'm giving you the truth.

640
00:35:15,190 --> 00:35:16,880
我不管你对此有什么感受
I don't care how that makes you feel.

641
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:19,250
但帮自己个忙  听进去我的话
But do yourself the favor of hearing what I said.

642
00:35:19,250 --> 00:35:22,270
-我听到了  -希望如此
- I heard you. - I hope so.

643
00:35:22,270 --> 00:35:24,190
我不能背叛自己  那我成什么了
I can't betray myself. What would I be then?

644
00:35:24,190 --> 00:35:26,370
政客  你本就是政客
You'd be a politician. And that's what you are.

645
00:35:26,370 --> 00:35:28,490
让其他人去吼叫呐喊吧
Let the others do all the yelling and screaming.

646
00:35:28,490 --> 00:35:30,570
你想要改变  就得学会妥协
You want change? Then learn how to compromise.

647
00:35:30,570 --> 00:35:32,070
成熟一点  迈克尔
Be a fucking adult about this, Michael.

648
00:35:32,080 --> 00:35:34,540
我得想想  好吗  我需要时间
I need to think. Okay? I need time.

649
00:35:37,070 --> 00:35:39,190
飞机明天就起飞了
The plane leaves tomorrow.

650
00:35:39,190 --> 00:35:41,940
你回去吧  我需要时间独自想想
You should go back. I need time to think alone.

651
00:35:41,950 --> 00:35:44,930
-清空思绪  -你不走  我也不走
- Clear my head. - I'm not leaving here without you.

652
00:35:44,930 --> 00:35:46,250
我需要时间
I need time!

653
00:35:48,180 --> 00:35:50,740
你躺一会儿吧
Just... lie down for a little bit.

654
00:35:50,740 --> 00:35:52,750
休息一下
Just get some rest.

655
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:55,400
-我不想再跟你争了  -好吧
- I just can't talk anymore. - Okay.

656
00:35:56,860 --> 00:35:58,180
我躺会儿
Okay, I will.

657
00:36:00,050 --> 00:36:01,210
就一会儿
For a few minutes.

658
00:36:42,090 --> 00:36:42,750
谢谢
Thanks.

659
00:36:56,740 --> 00:36:58,220
这病现在可以治的
There's treatment now.

660
00:36:59,500 --> 00:37:00,680
最让我生气的
The thing that angers me the most

661
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:02,240
是我让她这么对我
is that I let her do this to me.

662
00:37:09,210 --> 00:37:11,280
你对你前任也是这个感觉吗
Did you feel that way about your ex?

663
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:12,940
那痛苦能把你吞噬
The pain that just consumes you?

664
00:37:13,350 --> 00:37:14,660
有一阵吧
For a while, yeah.

665
00:37:16,130 --> 00:37:17,670
心情不好时还能感觉到
Still, on bad days.

666
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:26,910
她什么样
What was she like?

667
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:30,450
抱歉  你不非得...
Sorry, you don't have to...

668
00:37:30,450 --> 00:37:31,730
没事  我不介意
No, I don't mind.

669
00:37:33,240 --> 00:37:34,570
她...
She was...

670
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:39,570
她以前挺不容易
She'd had a tough life.

671
00:37:40,130 --> 00:37:42,610
有很多负担  我之前也是
She had a lot of baggage. Which I did, too.

672
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:48,420
我们起初只是朋友  后来搬到一起住
We started out as friends and then we moved in together.

673
00:37:49,770 --> 00:37:51,510
然后就发生了
And then it just happened.

674
00:37:52,100 --> 00:37:53,230
我们相爱了
We fell in love.

675
00:37:55,330 --> 00:37:56,720
我说不清
And I don't know, I guess...

676
00:37:58,990 --> 00:38:00,660
跟她在一起  我觉得自己更强大了
I felt stronger with her.

677
00:38:01,860 --> 00:38:03,490
我觉得她也有这种感觉
And I think she felt the same way.

678
00:38:05,620 --> 00:38:08,170
或许是我天真
And I guess maybe it was naive,

679
00:38:08,170 --> 00:38:11,760
但我以为我们携手前进  可以放下那些过去
but I thought that together, we could let go of all that baggage.

680
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:14,290
就一起做我们自己
Then we'd just be us.

681
00:38:17,410 --> 00:38:18,720
那她为什么离开了
Well, why did she leave?

682
00:38:21,430 --> 00:38:23,940
她说这一切太快了
She said everything was happening too quickly.

683
00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:31,250
你之后再联络过她吗
Have you spoken to her... since?

684
00:38:33,650 --> 00:38:36,690
没有  她再也不去团契了
Nope. She stopped coming to the fellowship.

685
00:38:38,260 --> 00:38:40,190
我去过她公寓一次
I stopped by her apartment once,

686
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:42,220
房东说她走了
her landlord said she was gone.

687
00:38:43,790 --> 00:38:45,510
你完全不知道她在哪吗
Just no idea where she is?

688
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:54,580
我们以前会躺在床上  幻想如果有选择
We used to lie in bed and fantasize about where we'd go

689
00:38:54,580 --> 00:38:59,220
我们会去哪  巴黎  澳大利亚  廷巴克图
if we could go anywhere. Paris, Australia, Timbuktu.

690
00:39:01,780 --> 00:39:04,910
瑞秋就这样  渴望远走高飞  我并不需要
That was Rachel, the far-off places. I didn't need that.

691
00:39:12,170 --> 00:39:13,360
你想去哪
Where would you go?

692
00:39:17,750 --> 00:39:19,220
希门尼斯山路
The Jimenez Trail.

693
00:39:20,070 --> 00:39:21,170
在哪啊
Where is that?

694
00:39:21,770 --> 00:39:22,850
新墨西哥州
New Mexico.

695
00:39:23,970 --> 00:39:25,710
穿过整个州
Cuts across the whole state.

696
00:39:25,710 --> 00:39:29,550
一路上有温泉  瀑布
It's got hot springs and waterfalls.

697
00:39:31,430 --> 00:39:33,770
我们以前曾说要去  徒步
We used to say we'd go there, hike it,

698
00:39:33,770 --> 00:39:36,950
找个好地方  建个小屋
find a good spot, build a cabin.

699
00:39:41,930 --> 00:39:45,700
抱歉  不该净说我的事
I'm sorry, we shouldn't be talking about me.

700
00:39:45,930 --> 00:39:46,890
是我问的
I asked.

701
00:39:47,970 --> 00:39:49,420
茶闻着挺香
That tea smells good.

702
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:51,530
我也来杯好了
I think I'll have some, too.

703
00:40:19,380 --> 00:40:20,770
可以
This looks good.

704
00:40:20,770 --> 00:40:22,920
-每字每句吗  -当然
- You say every word. - Of course.

705
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:24,800
然后直接带他上飞机
And then you take him directly to the plane.

706
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:27,680
维克多  谢谢你
Viktor... thank you.

707
00:40:30,830 --> 00:40:32,110
但是捷克共和国
But the Czech Republic,

708
